title: Anaerobic
description: Anaerobic training is a training in which the source of energy is not based on oxygen. Anaerobic exertion is performed at maximum intensity, while bouncing a pulse for a short period of time (up to three minutes). Common anaerobic workouts are weightlifting, iron ball throwing, sprint running, high or long jump and others.

title: Kids

title: Aerobic
description: Aerobic exercise is physical activity such as walking, running, cycling, swimming, squashing - and any other activity in which the cardiovascular and respiratory systems are used significantly to supply energy that activates large muscle groups in low-medium or high-intensity intensity - for a long period of time. relatively.

title: Pilates
description: Pilates largely avoids high impact, high power output, and heavy muscular and skeletal loading.
